HEADWORD: Kipskin
<hw>Kip"skin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Kip</ets> +
<ets>skin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Leather prepared from the skin of young or
small cattle, intermediate in grade between calfskin and
cowhide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

